sentences: Johannes Heer of Glarus (1489–1553) was a song composer and copyist, and later minister in the Reformed Church.
An edition, Das Liederbuch des Johannes Heer von Glarus, was published as part of the series Schweizerische Musikdenkmaler Basel, 1967.
Recordings of selections were made by the Huelgas Ensemble (1977) and the Ludwig Senfl Ensemble (1991).
